Scripting (EVAL / EVALSHA / SCRIPT)

Goblin Core embeds the Lua runtime and the standard Lua scripting helper
libraries. Each is vendored from its own public upstream under third_party/ and
retains its original copyright notice and permissive (MIT / BSD-style) license:

  Lua 5.1.5            Copyright (C) 1994-2012 Lua.org, PUC-Rio (MIT)
                       https://www.lua.org/            third_party/lua/COPYRIGHT
  lua-cjson 2.1.0      Copyright (C) 2010-2012 Mark Pulford (MIT)
                       https://github.com/mpx/lua-cjson third_party/lua-cjson/LICENSE
  lua-cmsgpack         Copyright (C) 2012 Salvatore Sanfilippo (BSD-2-Clause)
                       https://github.com/antirez/lua-cmsgpack
  Lua struct           Copyright (C) 2010-2012 Lua.org, PUC-Rio (MIT)
                       https://www.inf.puc-rio.br/~roberto/struct/
  LuaBitOp             Copyright (C) 2008-2012 Mike Pall (MIT)
                       https://bitop.luajit.org/

The two-clause BSD / MIT notices are carried in the respective source files.

The EVAL / EVALSHA / SCRIPT command family, the `redis` (and `server`) Lua API
table, and the RESP<->Lua value conversion were written independently from the
public Redis scripting specification. No Redis (or Valkey/Dragonfly) source code
was consulted or copied; the helper libraries above are the same independent
upstream projects that other engines also bundle.

A second, independent interpreter powers the LUAU.EVAL / LUAU.EVALSHA /
LUAU.SCRIPT command family. It embeds the Luau runtime (the minimal Common + Ast
+ Bytecode + Compiler + VM subset, without the CodeGen JIT or the Analysis type
checker), vendored under third_party/luau/ from its own public upstream:

  Luau                 Copyright (C) 2019-2024 Roblox Corporation
                       Copyright (C) 1994-2019 Lua.org, PUC-Rio (MIT)
                       https://github.com/luau-lang/luau
                       third_party/luau/LICENSE.txt (and lua_LICENSE.txt)

The LUAU.* command handlers and their `redis` API binding (src/luau_script.cpp)
were likewise written from the public scripting specification, not from any other
engine's source.

A third, independent interpreter powers the WREN.EVAL / WREN.EVALSHA /
WREN.SCRIPT command family, embedding the Wren scripting language, vendored under
third_party/wren/ from its own public upstream:

  Wren                 Copyright (C) 2013-2021 Robert Nystrom and Wren
                       Contributors (MIT)
                       https://wren.io  https://github.com/wren-lang/wren
                       third_party/wren/LICENSE

The WREN.* command handlers, the foreign `Redis` class binding, and the
Wren<->RESP value conversion (src/wren_script.cpp) were written from the public
Wren embedding documentation.

A fourth interpreter powers the TCL.EVAL / TCL.EVALSHA / TCL.SCRIPT command
family, embedding Jim Tcl (a small, embeddable Tcl), vendored under
third_party/jimtcl/ from its own public upstream:

  Jim Tcl              Copyright (c) 2005-2025 Salvatore Sanfilippo, Steve Bennett,
                       and other Jim Tcl contributors (BSD-2-Clause)
                       https://jim.tcl.tk  https://github.com/msteveb/jimtcl
                       third_party/jimtcl/LICENSE

Only the interpreter core plus the stdlib and tclcompat Tcl libraries are
vendored; third_party/jimtcl/jimautoconf.h is a hand-written portable config so
the subset builds without Jim's autosetup step. The TCL.* command handlers, the
`redis` Tcl command, and the Tcl<->RESP conversion (src/tcl_script.cpp) were
written from the public Jim Tcl embedding API.

A fifth interpreter powers the UPYTHON.EVAL / UPYTHON.EVALSHA / UPYTHON.SCRIPT
command family, embedding MicroPython. Its embed port (ports/embed) generated a
self-contained C tree, vendored under third_party/micropython/, from its own
public upstream:

  MicroPython          Copyright (c) 2013-2024 Damien P. George and contributors
                       (MIT)
                       https://micropython.org
                       https://github.com/micropython/micropython
                       third_party/micropython/LICENSE

The generated micropython_embed/ tree and its genhdr/ headers correspond to the
config in third_party/micropython/mpconfigport.h. The UPYTHON.* command handlers,
the `redis` Python module, and the Python<->RESP conversion (src/upython_script.cpp)
were written from the public MicroPython embedding API.
